\N<Man>Segi-san, where do you think you're going? I have a bad
feeling about this, but if you're planning to go to the
ruins ahead, I'd advise against it.

\N<Man>Even the entrance management of the ruins that have been in
this town for ages is now being handled by Luda's
soldiers...
<ActiveMessage:\C[1]■EV発生■>
<ActiveMessage:\C[1]■EV発生■>

\N<Man>Protective armor can be considered the bare minimum of
preparation, whether you're exploring ruins or fighting in
the training grounds.

\N<Man>There are still those in the city who attempt to resist the
soldiers of Luda, but it's such a nuisance. I keep saying
we should avoid pointless conflicts...

\N<Segi>...I wonder if the meeting is over by now. Let's head to the
management office...

<ActiveMessage:\C[1]■EV発生■>
\N<Segi>Rozaro-san.

\N<Rozaro>Segi-san, what are you doing in a place like this? Beyond
here is only the lakebed ruins under Luda's control and
their outpost...
\N<Segi>That is... well...

\N<Rozaro>...Could it be that you're trying to enter the ruins? Even
so, why would you...

\N<Rozaro>Don't tell me... it's because of our earlier conversation?
Are you saying that you've come to this decision because of
me?

\N<Rozaro>To protect Yuia and Riia, to stand up against Luda, you
believe you must also be strong...?

\N<Segi>Certainly... that might be part of it. But that's not the
only reason...
\N<Rozaro>...Can you tell me what you mean?

\N<Segi>In the past, I... entrusted something very important to
someone else, and as a result, I lost everything.

\N<Segi>By leaving important matters to important people... I lost
everything.
\N<Rozaro>Segi-san...

\N<Segi>...This time, I don't want it to end up like that. I don't
want to lose him by making Yuia-sama bear everything.

\N<Segi>It might be selfish of me. I think it would be better to
entrust everything to Yuia-sama and give up on my personal
sentiments.

\N<Segi>But... I also don't want to give up on believing that there
are things I can do.
\N<Segi>Is that... strange?

\N<Rozaro>No... there's nothing strange about it. What you're saying
is very noble. It's worthy of praise.
\N<Rozaro>However... do Yuia and Riia know about your decision?
\N<Segi>...No.
\N<Rozaro>...
\N<Segi>...

\N<Rozaro>...Understood, let's keep what you and I discussed here a
secret between us. After all, it's not really a matter for
an outsider like me to interfere with.
\N<Segi>...Thank you very much.

\N<Rozaro>However... I can't just let you go without saying anything.
Would you at least accept this?
\N<Segi>What is this...?

\N<Rozaro>You probably won't be able to enter the ruins directly even
if you go to Luda's outpost. First, they will suggest that
you go to an assessment facility to measure your aptitude
and strength.
\N<Segi>An assessment facility...?

\N<Rozaro>This will surely be of use to you then. So please, take it.
Consider it a modest parting gift for someone heading into
danger.

\N<Segi>...If that's the case, I gratefully accept. Thank you,
Rozaro-san.

\N<Rozaro>...Listen, Segi-san. Be very careful. Among the monsters
roaming inside the ruins are those with special self-defense
instincts to protect themselves.
\N<Segi>Understood. I appreciate your advice.

\N<Rozaro>And... if Luda's soldiers question you, just say you're a
warrior participating in the training assembly. That's why
you're entering the ruins.
\N<Segi>Understood. Thank you for everything.

\N<Rozaro>It's fine... This is all I can do. At least I'll be praying
for your safety...
